				<div id="bodyContent" class="vector-body" aria-labelledby="firstHeading" data-mw-ve-target-container>
					<div class="vector-body-before-content">
							<div class="mw-indicators">
		</div>

						<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
					</div>
					<div id="contentSub"><div id="mw-content-subtitle"></div></div>
					
					
					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><figure typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Coat_of_arms_of_the_Council_of_Heraldry_and_Vexillology.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Coat_of_arms_of_the_Council_of_Heraldry_and_Vexillology.svg/192px-Coat_of_arms_of_the_Council_of_Heraldry_and_Vexillology.svg.png" decoding="async" width="192" height="211" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Coat_of_arms_of_the_Council_of_Heraldry_and_Vexillology.svg/288px-Coat_of_arms_of_the_Council_of_Heraldry_and_Vexillology.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Coat_of_arms_of_the_Council_of_Heraldry_and_Vexillology.svg/384px-Coat_of_arms_of_the_Council_of_Heraldry_and_Vexillology.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="660" /></a><figcaption>The <a href="/wiki/Council_of_Heraldry_and_Vexillology" title="Council of Heraldry and Vexillology">Council of Heraldry and Vexillology</a> is in charge of supervising the granting and recording of non-noble arms in the <a href="/wiki/French_Community_of_Belgium" title="French Community of Belgium">French Community of Belgium</a>.</figcaption></figure><p><b>Burgher arms</b> or <b>bourgeois arms</b> are <a href="/wiki/Coat_of_arms" title="Coat of arms">coats of arms</a> borne by persons of the <i><a href="/wiki/Burgher_(title)" class="mw-redirect" title="Burgher (title)">burgher</a></i> social class of <a href="/wiki/Europe" title="Europe">Europe</a> since the <a href="/wiki/Middle_Ages" title="Middle Ages">Middle Ages</a> (usually called <i><a href="/wiki/Bourgeoisie" title="Bourgeoisie">bourgeois</a></i> in English). By definition, however, the term is alien to <a href="/wiki/British_heraldry" class="mw-redirect" title="British heraldry">British heraldry</a>, which follows other rules.
</p><p>In some European countries, certain armorial bearings have traditionally been restricted to a particular social class (usually the <a href="/wiki/Nobility" title="Nobility">nobility</a>), e.g. the use of <a href="/wiki/Supporters_(heraldry)" class="mw-redirect" title="Supporters (heraldry)">supporters</a> in <a href="/wiki/Coat_of_arms#United_Kingdom" title="Coat of arms">Great Britain</a>, <a href="/wiki/Tincture_(heraldry)" title="Tincture (heraldry)">tinctures</a> in <a href="/wiki/Portuguese_heraldry" title="Portuguese heraldry">Portugal</a> or <a href="/wiki/Coronets" class="mw-redirect" title="Coronets">coronets</a> in <a href="/wiki/Swedish_heraldry#Noble_arms" title="Swedish heraldry">Sweden</a>. Notwithstanding, in most countries outside the <a href="/wiki/United_Kingdom" title="United Kingdom">United Kingdom</a>, any individual, family and community has usually been free to adopt arms and use them as they please, provided they refrain from wrongfully assuming the preexisting arms of another.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> In addition to the <a href="/wiki/Bourgeoisie" title="Bourgeoisie">bourgeoisie</a>, <a href="/wiki/Peasant" title="Peasant">peasants</a> sometimes made use of this tradition.<sup class="noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style="white-space:nowrap;">&#91;<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources. (August 2013)">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup> Arms of the <a href="/wiki/Clergy" title="Clergy">clergy</a> are classified as <a href="/wiki/Ecclesiastical_heraldry" title="Ecclesiastical heraldry">ecclesiastical heraldry</a>. 
</p><p>Use of coats of arms by burghers and <a href="/wiki/Artisan" title="Artisan">artisans</a> began during the 13th century and in the 14th century some peasants took to using arms.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The arms of burghers bore a far wider variety of <a href="/wiki/Charge_(heraldry)" title="Charge (heraldry)">charges</a> than the arms of <a href="/wiki/Nobility" title="Nobility">nobility</a> like everyday objects, and particularly <a href="/wiki/Tool" title="Tool">tools</a>. <a href="/wiki/House_mark" title="House mark">House marks</a> are another type charges usually only used in burgher arms. Most widespread burgher heraldry was and still is found in <a href="/wiki/Belgian_heraldry" title="Belgian heraldry">Belgium</a>, <a href="/wiki/German_heraldry" title="German heraldry">Germany</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Swiss_heraldry&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Swiss heraldry (page does not exist)">Switzerland</a> and in the <a href="/wiki/Dutch_heraldry" title="Dutch heraldry">Netherlands</a>. In the latter only a small percentage of the existing arms belong to the nobility.<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>Crest-<a href="/wiki/Coronet" title="Coronet">coronets</a> in burgher arms are correct only if the arms were granted by a <a href="/wiki/Sovereign" title="Sovereign">sovereign</a> and the coronet is explicitly mentioned in the grant.<sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<meta property="mw:PageProp/toc" />
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="By_country">By country</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Burgher_arms&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: By country"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Belgium">Belgium</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Burgher_arms&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Belgium"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main article: <a href="/wiki/Belgian_heraldry" title="Belgian heraldry">Belgian heraldry</a></div>
<p>Bourgeois arms, such as those of the <a href="/wiki/Bourgeois_of_Brussels" title="Bourgeois of Brussels">bourgeois of Brussels</a>, were, and remain, common in Belgium and were granted except during the <a href="/wiki/French_Revolution" title="French Revolution">French Revolutionary</a> period and subsequent <a href="/wiki/French_First_Republic" title="French First Republic">republic</a>.
</p><p>Men admitted to the <a href="/wiki/Seven_Noble_Houses_of_Brussels" title="Seven Noble Houses of Brussels">Seven Noble Houses of Brussels</a>, many of whom were <i>not</i> noble, members of the <a href="/wiki/Guilds_of_Brussels" title="Guilds of Brussels">Guilds of Brussels</a>, and of the <a href="/wiki/Bourgeois_of_Brussels" title="Bourgeois of Brussels">Brussels Bourgeoisie</a>, were also granted or assumed arms.
</p><p>Today, the <a href="/wiki/Council_of_Heraldry_and_Vexillology" title="Council of Heraldry and Vexillology">Council of Heraldry and Vexillology</a> for the <a href="/wiki/French_Community_of_Belgium" title="French Community of Belgium">French Community</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Flemish_Heraldic_Council" title="Flemish Heraldic Council">Flemish Heraldic Council</a> for the <a href="/wiki/Flemish_Community" title="Flemish Community">Flemish Community</a> grant a <a href="/wiki/Helmet_(heraldry)" title="Helmet (heraldry)">helm</a> with torse, <a href="/wiki/Crest_(heraldry)" title="Crest (heraldry)">crest</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Mantling" title="Mantling">mantling</a> as well as a <a href="/wiki/Motto" title="Motto">motto</a> as external ornaments of the <a href="/wiki/Escutcheon_(heraldry)" title="Escutcheon (heraldry)">shield</a>. The additaments reserved for the nobility, such as crowned helmets and rank <a href="/wiki/Crown_(heraldry)" title="Crown (heraldry)">crowns</a>, <a href="/wiki/Supporter" title="Supporter">supporters</a> and supports, <a href="/wiki/Banner" title="Banner">banners</a> and <a href="/wiki/Battle_cry" title="Battle cry">battle cries</a>, mantles and pavilions, are prohibited.<sup id="cite_ref-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-5">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<p><b>Examples of Belgian bourgeois arms:</b></p><ul class="gallery mw-gallery-traditional">
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Armoiries_famille_be_de_Keghel.svg" class="mw-file-description" title="Arms of the de Keghel family, Bourgeois of Brussels until the 16th century."><img alt="Arms of the de Keghel family, Bourgeois of Brussels until the 16th century." src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Armoiries_famille_be_de_Keghel.svg/115px-Armoiries_famille_be_de_Keghel.svg.png" decoding="async" width="115" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Armoiries_famille_be_de_Keghel.svg/173px-Armoiries_famille_be_de_Keghel.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Armoiries_famille_be_de_Keghel.svg/230px-Armoiries_famille_be_de_Keghel.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="750" data-file-height="781" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">Arms of the de Keghel family, <a href="/wiki/Bourgeois_of_Brussels" title="Bourgeois of Brussels">Bourgeois of Brussels</a> until the 16th century.</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Pipenpoy_arms.svg" class="mw-file-description" title="Arms of the Pipenpoy family, an old Patrician family of Brussels."><img alt="Arms of the Pipenpoy family, an old Patrician family of Brussels." src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/14/Pipenpoy_arms.svg/103px-Pipenpoy_arms.svg.png" decoding="async" width="103" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/14/Pipenpoy_arms.svg/154px-Pipenpoy_arms.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/14/Pipenpoy_arms.svg/206px-Pipenpoy_arms.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="410" data-file-height="478" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">Arms of the <a href="/wiki/Pipenpoy_family" title="Pipenpoy family">Pipenpoy family</a>, an old <a href="/wiki/Patrician_(post-Roman_Europe)" title="Patrician (post-Roman Europe)">Patrician</a> family of Brussels.</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Dewandre_achievement.svg" class="mw-file-description" title="Arms of the Dewandre family, originally from Liège."><img alt="Arms of the Dewandre family, originally from Liège." src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/Dewandre_achievement.svg/104px-Dewandre_achievement.svg.png" decoding="async" width="104" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/Dewandre_achievement.svg/156px-Dewandre_achievement.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/Dewandre_achievement.svg/208px-Dewandre_achievement.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="512" data-file-height="591" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">Arms of the Dewandre family, originally from <a href="/wiki/Li%C3%A8ge" title="Liège">Liège</a>.</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Blason_de_la_famille_Poelaert_(Bruxelles).svg" class="mw-file-description" title="Arms of the Poelaert family, bourgeois of Brussels."><img alt="Arms of the Poelaert family, bourgeois of Brussels." src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/36/Blason_de_la_famille_Poelaert_%28Bruxelles%29.svg/109px-Blason_de_la_famille_Poelaert_%28Bruxelles%29.svg.png" decoding="async" width="109" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/36/Blason_de_la_famille_Poelaert_%28Bruxelles%29.svg/164px-Blason_de_la_famille_Poelaert_%28Bruxelles%29.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/36/Blason_de_la_famille_Poelaert_%28Bruxelles%29.svg/218px-Blason_de_la_famille_Poelaert_%28Bruxelles%29.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="660" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">Arms of the <a href="/wiki/Poelaert_family" title="Poelaert family">Poelaert family</a>, bourgeois of Brussels.</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Van_der_Meulen_arms_variant_1.svg" class="mw-file-description" title="Arms of the Van der Meulen family"><img alt="Arms of the Van der Meulen family" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/Van_der_Meulen_arms_variant_1.svg/109px-Van_der_Meulen_arms_variant_1.svg.png" decoding="async" width="109" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/Van_der_Meulen_arms_variant_1.svg/164px-Van_der_Meulen_arms_variant_1.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/Van_der_Meulen_arms_variant_1.svg/218px-Van_der_Meulen_arms_variant_1.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="660" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">Arms of the <a href="/wiki/Van_der_Meulen_family" title="Van der Meulen family">Van der Meulen family</a></div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Armorial_de_la_Gilde_Drapi%C3%A8re_Bruxelles_02.jpg" class="mw-file-description" title="Roll of arms of the Drapery Court of Brussels, some of which are Bourgeois arms."><img alt="Roll of arms of the Drapery Court of Brussels, some of which are Bourgeois arms." src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Armorial_de_la_Gilde_Drapi%C3%A8re_Bruxelles_02.jpg/78px-Armorial_de_la_Gilde_Drapi%C3%A8re_Bruxelles_02.jpg" decoding="async" width="78" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Armorial_de_la_Gilde_Drapi%C3%A8re_Bruxelles_02.jpg/117px-Armorial_de_la_Gilde_Drapi%C3%A8re_Bruxelles_02.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Armorial_de_la_Gilde_Drapi%C3%A8re_Bruxelles_02.jpg/156px-Armorial_de_la_Gilde_Drapi%C3%A8re_Bruxelles_02.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2452" data-file-height="3767" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext"><a href="/wiki/Roll_of_arms" title="Roll of arms">Roll of arms</a> of the <a href="/wiki/Drapery_Court_of_Brussels" title="Drapery Court of Brussels">Drapery Court of Brussels</a>, some of which are <a href="/wiki/Bourgeois_of_Brussels" title="Bourgeois of Brussels">Bourgeois</a> arms.</div>
		</li>
</ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="France">France</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Burgher_arms&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: France"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p><a href="/w/index.php?title=Ancient_French_bourgeoisie&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Ancient French bourgeoisie (page does not exist)">ancient French bourgeoisie</a> [<b><a href="https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Liste_de_familles_subsistantes_d%27ancienne_bourgeoisie_fran%C3%A7aise" class="extiw" title="fr:Liste de familles subsistantes d&#39;ancienne bourgeoisie française">fr</a></b>] arms used to be common in <a href="/wiki/France" title="France">France</a>, but they disappeared in the <a href="/wiki/French_Revolution" title="French Revolution">French Revolution</a>, which was hostile to heraldry. In the end of the 17th century, an attempt was made to list all arms in <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Armorial_g%C3%A9n%C3%A9ral_(of_France)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Armorial général (of France) (page does not exist)">Armorial général</a></i> as a device to increase tax revenue. When the attempt failed, in order to force people to pay tax, arms were given to many burghers who had never had them. These arms were never used by their recipients.<sup id="cite_ref-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-6">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> In France burgher arms are not supposed to have a helmet.
</p>
<p><b>Examples of French bourgeois arms:</b></p><ul class="gallery mw-gallery-traditional">
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Blason_de_la_famille_Martinot_(Paris).svg" class="mw-file-description" title="Arms of the Martinot family, famous clockmaker family of Paris."><img alt="Arms of the Martinot family, famous clockmaker family of Paris." src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/Blason_de_la_famille_Martinot_%28Paris%29.svg/109px-Blason_de_la_famille_Martinot_%28Paris%29.svg.png" decoding="async" width="109" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/Blason_de_la_famille_Martinot_%28Paris%29.svg/164px-Blason_de_la_famille_Martinot_%28Paris%29.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/Blason_de_la_famille_Martinot_%28Paris%29.svg/218px-Blason_de_la_famille_Martinot_%28Paris%29.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="600" data-file-height="660" /></a></span></div>
